        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 24 at 4:18PM CDT by NWS Paducah KY</headline>
        <description>At 418 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
New Harmony, or 15 miles southeast of Albion, moving northeast at 15
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Griffin and New Harmony.

This includes Interstate 64 in Indiana between Mile Markers 3 and 9.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
